# Pulling from a registry

A **registry** stores and serves images. Default: **Docker Hub**.

```bash
docker pull nginx:1.27
```

The daemon downloads the image's **layers** (skipping any you have), caches them locally ‚Äî then `docker run` starts instantly, offline.

## Reading an image reference

```
registry-1.docker.io / library / nginx : 1.27
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ registry ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îînamespace‚îò ‚îîname‚îò ‚îîtag‚îò
```

- **registry** ‚Äî defaults to Docker Hub.
- **namespace** ‚Äî the owner; official images live under `library/` (never typed).
- **name** ‚Äî the repository.
- **tag** ‚Äî a version label, defaults to **`latest`**.

`latest` is just a **conventional tag**, *not* magically newest ‚Äî **pin real versions** in production.

So `nginx` means `docker.io/library/nginx:latest`. Pull = download; **push** = upload (module 07).
